        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 7:51PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 748 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking multiple slow-moving
scattered thunderstorms across far northern Illinois. Additional
storms are expected to develop across the Special Weather Statement
area.

HAZARD...Localized wind gusts up to 50 mph, frequent lightning, and
torrential downpours.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Torrential downpours may lead to
localized flooding of low-lying areas.

Locations that may be impacted include...

Forreston, Byron, Rockford, Belvidere, Kirkland, Rochelle,  Crystal
Lake, Mundelein, Arlington Heights, and Elgin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
